The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Six armed men snatched cash and gold worth Rs 50,000 from a trader at Metro Park of Haridevpur, in Thakurpukur, on Friday. Amal Saha Roy, a dealer of building material, was closing his shop when the gangsters arrived on motorcycles. They even took away a cellphone from one of Roys employees. Roys gold chain, ring and Rs 15,000 was taken by the youths.     The mutilated body of a 30-year-old man was found in a sack in Rabindra Nagar, on the southern fringes of the city, on Friday. Mahesh Mahato, the employee of a private organisation, was a resident of Akrapara. Police said part of his body was was burnt. Two persons were arrested.     A middle-aged man was crushed under the rear wheels of a private bus at the Hazra crossing on Friday evening. Police said Om Prakash Sharma, 43, was trying to cross the road when the bus knocked him down. He was rushed to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared brought dead.    Three Manipuri youths, who were arrested by Assam police in connection with a car theft case, were brought to the city late on Thursday. The three had stolen a Honda City from Bowbazar on March 25, said an officer. They were intercepted at a checkpost in Siliguri and the officers found the registration of the vehicle to be fake.    Samar Das, 58, an employee of Calcutta Port Trusts Centenary Hospital, was found hanging from the ceiling of his quarters in Taratala on Thursday. No suicide note was found. Police have ruled out foul play.                                                                                                                                                                 
